According to research slated for release May, 30th by the Oxford University-based Pathways for Prosperity Commission on Technology and Inclusive Development, well-considered investments in digital technology can be transformational for health and education services across the developing world, but too often they fail to deliver impact at scale. For more CNBC Africa is joined by Prof Benno Ndulu, former Governor of the Central Bank of Tanzania.

